ccording to former and current culture team members, shows little interest =
in any of the fashion content, despite it being a large part of what he ove=
rsees. Ball=E2=80=99s mag<em> does</em> feel different from the previous it=
eration of<em> WSJ</em>. (In some ways, it reminds me more of the supplemen=
t
<strong>Tina</strong> <strong>Gaudoin</strong> launched all the way back in=
 2008.)=C2=A0<br/><br/>One <em>Journal</em> insider suggested that this fur=
