=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">I remember us all sittin=
g down and thinking the Nap Dress might be a flash in the pan, and if so, h=
ow do we maintain the business that we love and that we know is more than j=
ust one product? So it=E2=80=99s wild for it to be 2025, and to look at our=
 stats, and to see the Nap Dress in the low 20s as a percentage of our busi=
ness. I actually think it gives us a tremendous safety net. <br/><br/>For
a retail business in a challenging macroeconomic climate, I look to brands =
like Ralph Lauren or Tory Burch that are really building meaningful, though=
tful businesses off of some amazing hero products. I also look at our custo=
mers, the top 15 percent of whom own over <em>14 dresses</em>. We call thos=
e customers =E2=80=9CNap Dress Nation=E2=80=9D=E2=80=94our most loyal custo=
mers. Some of them have every single one we=E2=80=99ve ever created, and we=
 definitely cater to that group, but then we also don=E2=80=99t want to ali=
enate either
group.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>You have a complex brand, and I=E2=80=99=
ve noticed that there are certain hallmarks=E2=80=94calling everyone =E2=80=
=9Cbestie,=E2=80=9D and details like a particular bow design=E2=80=94that b=
ring your customer along with you on the journey without alienating the per=
son that=E2=80=99s not in the know.</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin=
-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">
I want a customer who maybe had heard about Hill House but never actually t=
ried it to be scrolling on, you know, their website of choice and see a rea=
lly cute dress at a great price that ships tomorrow and be like, <em>Great,=
 I=E2=80=99ll try it</em>. I don=E2=80=99t need them to know any of the lor=
e or the lingo, because at the end of the day, our true purpose is to give =
people these amazing clothes at really great price points that make them fe=
el incredible. Our K.P.I. on social media is =E2=80=9Cfun.=E2=80=9D We=E2=
=80=99re not
tracking. We=E2=80=99re not trying to get people to be obsessed with the br=
and. There=E2=80=99s no big strategy. It=E2=80=99s natural for us, and it w=
ould be much harder if we weren=E2=80=99t part of that customer base, ourse=
lves.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>What=E2=80=99s the wholesale strategy? Is=
 there a person dedicated to it in-house?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;=
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">In 2=
024, wholesale was
about less than 5 percent of the business. In 2023, it was less than 2 perc=
ent, but we are just starting, so no, nobody in-house is dedicated. It=E2=
=80=99s still a shared function between our merch team and me. Our warehous=
e is focused on D.T.C. The operational aspect of wholesale for a D.T.C. bra=
nd is something that I don=E2=80=99t hear discussed a lot, but that can tak=
e <em>years</em> to get your business lined up for=E2=80=94not just being a=
ble to show market appointments, but being able to avoid chargebacks, which
are a massive, <em>massive</em> hit to young brands. My overarching goal is=
 that I want more people trying Hill House Home in person because I know th=
at=E2=80=99s where it sings. I can do all the magic online, but at the end =
of the day, it=E2=80=99s gonna sing so much better in person. I want to max=
imize that.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p =
style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>What=E2=80=99s on the horizon=
 for 2025, collab-wise?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;=
">=C2=A0
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">I think we=E2=80=99ve been sla=
cking on collabs. We have a few that we=E2=80=99ve signed recently that wil=
l be coming up starting in March. We=E2=80=99re working on a collab right n=
ow and we=E2=80=99re doing the prints and it=E2=80=99s just fun. We=E2=80=
=99re all just like, <em>I can=E2=80=99t wait to have this in my house</em>=
=2E It=E2=80=99s around that feeling of fu=
n, excitement, and freshness that p=
eople genuinely love. It arrives at your door, you get it in the store, and=
 you=E2=80=99re so happy. That=E2=80=99s a big K.P.I. for
us, and then also from a team perspective, something that we get really exc=
ited to talk about.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><=
p style=3D"margin:0;">I also think there=E2=80=99s a real business case for=
 testing new categories. We went from a home brand to a fashion brand, so I=
 don=E2=80=99t think that there are any limits in terms of what categories =
